<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-909-158  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 909 158.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 28 1989 v3 n35 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pentagon considers FTS 2000 a mixed blessing. (FederalTelecommunication System 2000 nationwide telephone system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Defense (DOD) has decided to make decisions on acase by case basis about whether or not to use the GeneralServices Administration-run FTS 2000 telecommunications system.andO;The DOD will put financial considerations at the forefront andwill use the FTS 2000 system only if it is the most cost effectivesolution.andP;  The DOD feels that the Warner Amendment exempts it fromusing the FTS 2000 system for traffic essential to nationalsecurity.andP;  For such secure transmissions the DOD will procure itsown fiber optic network for installation between DOD locations toprovide digital circuits for communication.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseFiber OpticsTelecommunicationsGovernment AgencyCommunications Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>